<br />
site 1:      Gondor def +1<br />
site 2:      initiative +3<br />
site 3:      add a threat to draw a card<br />
site 4:      remove 3 burdens to make archery +3<br />
site 5:      maneuver: 2 burdens or discard hand<br />
site 6:      regroupmove: wound everyone<br />
site 7:      6 comps, movelimit -1<br />
site 8:      remove 2 threats to play gollum and add          2 burdens<br />
site 9:      move to and add 3 threats.<br />
<br />
Yes! A easy Easterling deck, not quite my own. Just made it to try. But the fellowship I created myself. I thought it would be fun to do something with Bilbo the condition discarder. Then I read Pippins gametext. So the ammo for wasting conditions will stay around plus they make your fellowship a bit more fital. Gandalf gets at strenght 10 and will safe Faramir, Faramir will safe Pippin and Pippin wil safe your conditions. Frodo keeps Bilbo alive and so the circle is complete. That is also the main aim of the fellowship. Staying around long enough to kill the opponents fellowship. Might of Numenor takes either care of opponents conditions or heals your fellowship. <br />
<br /><br />
<br />
<br /><br />
Easterling Shadow is very familiair. Get some burdens on the fellowship and try kill them with captain. I’m considering to add Ships of great Draught for getting some fital cards back. Well let me know!<br />
